Here is a mini tutorial for how to easily apply 2d images to 3d shapes using openscad. 
-Extrude a dxf of the logo so its long enough to intersect the surface, and make full contact on all sides
-Use intersection() to leave only the point where the two objects intersect
-Apply the logo to the outside of a new copy of the item, taking care to keep a thin profile so support isnt required
Openscad had a huge problem with the klein bottle merge at first. I had to scale the bottle way way <em >way</em> down. 
Complete source code used to make the bottle:
intersection() {
scale([0.4,0.4,0.4]) rotate([90,0,0]) translate([-6,0.5,9]) linear_extrude( file="s67logo.dxf", height=7 );
import_stl("s67bottleforklienbottlesmall.stl", center=true); }
translate([0,0.2,0]) import_stl("s67bottleforklienbottlesmall.stl", center=true);
